JMS: Could people please make clear distinction between name-string (target of <nop>LinneanCore) and name (a relationship between a name-string and a named-object, would be expressed by TCS) throughout?  Otherwise it is too hard to follow (for non-native speakers at least).  Name-strings in <nop>LinneanCore domain are affected by combination for bi- or tri- nomen, but it is not conceptual issue just like difference between "I have" and "she has".  If 'generic', 'specific', 'infraspecific' are uncomfortable for their relevance to concept, we would say 'first_token', 'sencond_token' and 'third_token' instead.  Or, does the distincition between name-string and name contradict to TCS philosophy? -- 12 Nov 2004.
